question: A jewelry company offers a one-year warranty on all of its necklaces. The company knows that the average number of necklaces shipped to its customers per week is 250. Further, the company knows that the number of necklaces returned for warranty work across all products per week follows a Poisson distribution with a mean of 10, of which approximately one-sixth are necklaces. How many necklaces will the company receive for warranty work this week?

During a school project on wind power, Mia and her friends are trying to estimate the power generated by a small wind turbine. They know the power generated by the turbine can be modeled by the equation:

\( P(t) = 150 + 30 \sin \left( \frac{π}{6} t \right) \) watts

where \( t \) is the time in seconds after the turbine starts generating power. Mia and her team aim to calculate the average power output from \( t = 0 \) seconds to \( t = 12 \) seconds. Can you help them calculate the total average power output during this time period?

question: In a particular kingdom, there are three types of magical coins: Gold (G), Silver (S), and Bronze (B). A spell has been cast where every time a Gold coin is flipped, it doubles the number of Silver coins it has, but halves the number of Bronze coins; every time a Silver coin is flipped, it triples the number of Bronze coins it has, but reduces the number of Gold coins by half; and every time a Bronze coin is flipped, it creates two new Gold coins, but reduces the number of Silver coins to one-third. Initially, there are 50 Gold coins, 100 Silver coins, and 150 Bronze coins. How many flips are required so that at least one coin is flipped at least 10 times?
Find all prime numbers \( p \) and \( q \) such that the equation \( p^q + q^p = 10pq \) holds true.

If a dart lands randomly on the dartboard, what is the probability that it scores at least 3 points? Express your answer as a common fraction.
